### `package.json`

Currently identifies as `code-oss-dev` v1.99.3 (upstream VS Code OSS name). The `version` and `author` fields reference Microsoft. The `name`, `version`, `author`, `repository`, and `bugs` fields are candidates to update but **touching these affects build scripts and CI** ‚Äî leave alone for v0.1, revisit when we wire our own release pipeline.

### Files / folders to rename later (defer to Phase 2)

These are nice-to-have, not blocking:
- `void_icons/` ‚Üí `vselite_icons/` (after we have new icons)
- `.voidrules` ‚Üí `.vselite-rules` (after the content also gets edited)
- React component names with `Void` prefix ‚Äî `VoidOnboarding`, `VoidCommandBar`, `VoidSelectionHelper`, `VoidTooltip`. These are internal class names, never user-visible. Rename in a single sweep when we touch each component anyway.

### Files / strings to grep for

Run a single workspace search for case-insensitive `void` after Task 1 to surface anything missed. Expect a lot of false positives (`void` is a TS keyword, MIT license mentions, the word in code comments, etc.). Focus on:
- User-visible strings ("Welcome to Void", "Void Settings", chat placeholder text)
- About dialog content
- README files inside the repo
- Onboarding step text

